Package io.shiromi.saml.types

Class GenericType

java.lang.Object
io.shiromi.saml.types.AbstractType<Object>
io.shiromi.saml.types.GenericType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public final class GenericType extends AbstractType<Object>
Instances of the class GenericType carry a value of type Object, essentially acting as an Any type, as the same suggests, this class' sole purpose is to allow interchangeability between types and generification of types.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Shiromi

      public boolean isString()
      Checks if the value contained by this class is a String, use this to check for availability for casting to StringType 
      
      GenericType g = new GenericType("Foo");
      StringType s;

      if (g.isString()) s = g.stringType();

      • stringType(GenericType, boolean)

      whether this value is either a String, char or char[] or not
